Now I'll save the API data to a file using the file_operations_writer tool. I'll use the default file path "data/input.json" and assume the data from network_fetcher is available in the environment.

<tool_call>file_operations_writer
{
  "destination": "data/input.json",
  "data": {}
}
</tool_call>

I need to create the directory first. Since no dedicated directory creation tool is available, I'll use the file_operations_writer tool to create the directory by writing a file. I'll write an empty file to "data/.temp" to create the directory structure.

<tool_call>file_operations_writer
{
  "destination": "data/.temp",
  "data": {}
}
</tool_call>
